content:
In CRM Analytics, use a Filter node to remove rows that you don't need in your target. For example, filter case records to focus on escalated cases only. Filter values are case-sensitive.

To add a Filter node:

*   Select the Add Node button between two nodes or at the end of the recipe.
*   In the Add Node dialog box, select Filter.

A filter node adjacent to a direct data input node is marked with a lightning bolt and limits the number of records loaded into the recipe.

You can define a standard filter using conventional operators or add a custom filter expression for more granularity. If you define a filter condition on a dimension column, you can select a filter value from a list of values in your dataset.

To display current standard filter logic, click  and Add Standard Filter Logic. To edit the logic, click the pencil icon and build the filter logic with parenthesis and Boolean operators. Click Apply and Save the recipe.
title: Filtering Rows in CRM Analytics
